FBIS3-44171 "drafr017_c_94011" FBIS-AFR-94-017 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Communist Party Notes `Intelligence Networks' MB2501171694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 25 Jan 94 MB2501171694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The SACP [South African Communist Party] claims that the National Party [NP] is using intelligence networks to run a smear campaign for electioneering. A member of the SACP Central Committee, Mr. Jeremy Cronin, has called on the NP to confirm or deny that the SACP's facsimile and telephone lines have been tapped. He also called on the NP to explain its connection to the National Intelligence Service and to name all the Broederbond [Secret Afrikaner Brotherhood] members on its election list.
